      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai): bound Codex OAuth JSON and error response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`postTokenForm` in the OpenAI Codex OAuth flow reads the full token endpoint\nresponse body with `response.arrayBuffer()` before returning a cloned Response.\nA hostile or buggy endpoint could stream an unbounded response body, exhausting\ngateway memory, because the byte cap was applied *after* the unbounded clone.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe plugin SDK provides `readResponseWithLimit` (16 MiB capped Buffer read)\nfor this exact pattern. By moving the byte cap *inside* `postTokenForm`,\nbefore `release()`, the original guarded response is read under a hard size\nlimit and the unbounded `arrayBuffer()` path is eliminated.\n\nAdditional defense-in-depth: `readProviderJsonResponse` and\n`readResponseTextLimited` on the already-bounded cloned Response for caller-\nside safety.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-facing behavior change under normal operation. Oversized token\nendpoint responses now safely return a `{ type: \"failed\" }` result from the\nbounded `postTokenForm` instead of potentially exhausting memory before the\ncap runs.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-oauth-flow.runtime.test.ts` — 14\n  tests passed (10 existing + 4 new bounding tests)\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\n## Tests\n\n`extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-oauth-flow.runtime.test.ts` — 4 new tests:\n- caps oversized token exchange response at `postTokenForm` level\n- caps oversized token refresh response at `postTokenForm` level\n- rejects malformed token exchange JSON response\n- caps oversized error body on failed token exchange\n",
        "branch": "fix/openai-bound-oauth-json-response-reads",
